name: RNA polymerase II cis-regulatory region sequence-specific DNA binding
description: Interacting selectively and non-covalently with a specific upstream regulatory DNA sequence (transcription factor recognition sequence or binding site) located in cis relative to the transcription start site (i.e., on the same strand of DNA) of a gene transcribed by RNA polymerase II.

name: ubiquitin protein ligase activity
description: Catalysis of the transfer of ubiquitin to a substrate protein via the reaction X-ubiquitin + S -> X + S-ubiquitin, where X is either an E2 or E3 enzyme, the X-ubiquitin linkage is a thioester bond, and the S-ubiquitin linkage is an amide bond: an isopeptide bond between the C-terminal glycine of ubiquitin and the epsilon-amino group of lysine residues in the substrate or, in the linear extension of ubiquitin chains, a peptide bond the between the C-terminal glycine and N-terminal methionine of ubiquitin residues.

name: nuclease activity
description: Catalysis of the hydrolysis of ester linkages within nucleic acids.

name: transferase activity
description: Catalysis of the transfer of a group, e.g. a methyl group, glycosyl group, acyl group, phosphorus-containing, or other groups, from one compound (generally regarded as the donor) to another compound (generally regarded as the acceptor). Transferase is the systematic name for any enzyme of EC class 2.

name: N-acetylgalactosamine 4-O-sulfotransferase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: 3'-phosphoadenosine 5'-phosphosulfate + N-acetyl-D-galactosamine = adenosine 3',5'-bisphosphate + N-acetyl-D-galactosamine 4-sulfate.

name: peptide hormone binding
description: Interacting selectively and non-covalently with any peptide with hormonal activity in animals.

name: galactosylceramide sulfotransferase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: 3'-phosphoadenosine 5'-phosphosulfate + a galactosylceramide = adenosine 3',5'-bisphosphate + a galactosylceramidesulfate.

name: calcium-dependent cysteine-type endopeptidase activity
description: Catalysis of the hydrolysis of nonterminal peptide bonds in a polypeptide chain by a mechanism using a cysteine residue at the enzyme active center, and requiring the presence of calcium.

name: parathyroid hormone receptor activity
description: Combining with parathyroid hormone to initiate a change in cell activity.

name: voltage-gated calcium channel activity
description: Enables the transmembrane transfer of a calcium ion by a voltage-gated channel. A voltage-gated channel is a channel whose open state is dependent on the voltage across the membrane in which it is embedded.

name: SNAP receptor activity
description: Acting as a marker to identify a membrane and interacting selectively with one or more SNAREs on another membrane to mediate membrane fusion.

name: phosphatidylinositol-5-phosphate binding
description: Interacting selectively and non-covalently with phosphatidylinositol-5-phosphate, a derivative of phosphatidylinositol in which the inositol ring is phosphorylated at the 5' position.

name: phosphatidylinositol-3,4,5-trisphosphate 3-phosphatase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: phosphatidylinositol-3,4,5-trisphosphate + H2O = phosphatidylinositol-4,5-bisphosphate + phosphate.

name: ionotropic glutamate receptor binding
description: Interacting selectively and non-covalently with an ionotropic glutamate receptor. Ionotropic glutamate receptors bind glutamate and exert an effect through the regulation of ion channels.

name: Wnt-activated receptor activity
description: Combining with a Wnt protein and transmitting the signal across the plasma membrane to initiate a change in cell activity.

name: phospholipase binding
description: Interacting selectively and non-covalently with any phospholipase, enzymes that catalyze of the hydrolysis of a glycerophospholipid.

name: heparan sulfate proteoglycan binding
description: Interacting selectively and non-covalently with a heparan sulfate proteoglycan, any proteoglycan containing heparan sulfate as the glycosaminoglycan carbohydrate unit.

name: chondroitin 4-sulfotransferase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: 3'-phosphoadenosine 5'-phosphosulfate + chondroitin = adenosine 3',5'-bisphosphate + chondroitin 4'-sulfate.

name: galactose 3-O-sulfotransferase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: N-acetyllactosamine + 3'-phosphoadenosine 5'-phosphosulfate = 3-sulfo-N-acetyllactosamine + adenosine 3',5'-bisphosphate. N-acetyllactosamine residues are found in a number of different carbohydrate types. N-acetyllactosamine can also be written as Gal-beta-(1,4)-GlcNAc.

name: phosphatidylinositol-4-phosphate binding
description: Interacting selectively and non-covalently with phosphatidylinositol-4-phosphate, a derivative of phosphatidylinositol in which the inositol ring is phosphorylated at the 4' position.

name: protein tyrosine kinase binding
description: Interacting selectively and non-covalently with protein tyrosine kinase.

name: G-quadruplex RNA binding
description: Interacting selectively and non-covalently with G-quadruplex RNA structures, in which groups of four guanines adopt a flat, cyclic hydrogen-bonding arrangement known as a guanine tetrad.

name: dystroglycan binding
description: Interacting selectively and non-covalently with dystroglycan. Dystroglycan is glycoprotein found in non-muscle tissues as well as in muscle tissues, often in association with dystrophin. The native dystroglycan cleaved into two non-covalently associated subunits, alpha (N-terminal) and beta (C-terminal).

name: argininosuccinate synthase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: ATP + L-citrulline + L-aspartate = AMP + diphosphate + (N(omega)-L-arginino)succinate.

name: cystathionine gamma-lyase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: L-cystathionine + H2O = 2-oxobutanoate + L-cysteine + NH4+.

name: histidine decarboxylase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: L-histidine = histamine + CO2.

name: non-membrane spanning protein tyrosine phosphatase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: non-membrane spanning protein tyrosine phosphate + H2O = non-membrane spanning protein tyrosine + phosphate.

name: thioredoxin-disulfide reductase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: NADP(+) + thioredoxin = H(+) + NADPH + thioredoxin disulfide.

name: extracellularly glutamate-gated ion channel activity
description: Enables the transmembrane transfer of an ion by a channel that opens when glutamate is  bound by the channel complex or one of its constituent parts on the extracellular side of the plasma membrane.

name: cation transmembrane transporter activity
description: Enables the transfer of cation from one side of a membrane to the other.

name: growth hormone-releasing hormone receptor activity
description: Combining with growth hormone-releasing hormone to initiate a change in cell activity.

name: carbon-sulfur lyase activity
description: Catalysis of the elimination of hydrogen sulfide or substituted H2S.

name: sodium channel inhibitor activity
description: Stops, prevents, or reduces the activity of a sodium channel.

name: protein phosphatase binding
description: Interacting selectively and non-covalently with any protein phosphatase.

name: transmembrane receptor protein tyrosine kinase activator activity
description: Binds to and increases the activity of a transmembrane receptor protein tyrosine kinase.

name: transforming growth factor beta receptor, common-partner cytoplasmic mediator activity
description: A TGF-beta cytoplasmic mediator that forms a complex with a phosphorylated pathway-specific mediator. The heterocomplex translocates to the nucleus to regulate transcription.

name: D1 dopamine receptor binding
description: Interacting selectively and non-covalently with a D1 dopamine receptor.

name: heterotrimeric G-protein binding
description: Interacting selectively and non-covalently with a heterotrimeric G-protein.

name: lipoyl(octanoyl) transferase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: octanoyl-[acyl-carrier protein] + protein = protein N6-(octanoyl)lysine + acyl-carrier protein.

name: L-cystine L-cysteine-lyase (deaminating)
description: Catalysis of the reaction: L-cystine + H2O <=> pyruvate + NH3 + thiocysteine. Thiocysteine is also known as cysteine persulfide.

name: translation factor activity, non-nucleic acid binding
description: A translation regulator activity that does not involve binding to nucleic acids.

name: tropinone reductase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: NADP(+) + pseudotropine = H(+) + NADPH + tropinone.

name: phosphoserine residue binding
description: Interacting selectively and non-covalently with a phosphorylated serine residue within a protein.

name: peptide hormone receptor binding
description: Interacting selectively and non-covalently with a receptor for peptide hormones.

name: inositol-1,3,4,5-tetrakisphosphate 3-phosphatase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: inositol-1,3,4,5-tetrakisphosphate + H2O = inositol-1,4,5-trisphosphate + phosphate.

name: phosphatidylinositol-3,4-bisphosphate 3-phosphatase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: phosphatidylinositol-3,4-bisphosphate + H2O = phosphatidylinositol-4-phosphate + phosphate.

name: N(1),N(12)-diacetylspermine:oxygen oxidoreductase (3-acetamidopropanal-forming) activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: H(2)O + N(1),N(12)-diacetylspermine + O(2) = 3-acetamidopropanal + H(2)O(2) + N(1)-acetylspermidine.

name: spermidine:oxygen oxidoreductase (3-aminopropanal-forming) activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: H(2)O + O(2) + spermidine = 3-aminopropanal + H(2)O(2) + putrescine.

name: N1-acetylspermine:oxygen oxidoreductase (3-acetamidopropanal-forming) activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: H(2)O + N(1)-acetylspermine + O(2) = 3-acetamidopropanal + H(2)O(2) + spermidine.

name: N1-acetylspermidine:oxygen oxidoreductase (3-acetamidopropanal-forming) activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: H(2)O + N(1)-acetylspermidine + O(2) = 3-acetamidopropanal + H(2)O(2) + putrescine.

name: octanoyl transferase activity (acting on glycine-cleavage complex H protein)
description: Catalysis of the reaction: [glycine cleavage system lipoyl-carrier protein]-L-lysine + OCTANOYL-ACP = H+ + a [glycine-cleavage complex H protein] N6-octanoyl-L-lysine + a holo-[acyl-carrier protein]

name: (25S)-Delta(4)-dafachronate binding
description: Interacting selectively and non-covalently with (25S)-Delta(4)-dafachronate.

name: (25S)-Delta(7)-dafachronate binding
description: Interacting selectively and non-covalently with (25S)-Delta(7)-dafachronate.
